This class was inspired by a vertical transportation that moves people or goods between floors called _Elevator_. This class produces some navigation items that can be used to go to the next and previous chunks, step by step, just like [navigation buttons in an elevator](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storey "Storey – Wikipedia").

### Constructor

~~~ .xmp.php
Elevator($input, $chunk = 5, $index = 0, $path = true, $config = [], $NS = "");
~~~

Start by creating a new class construct:

~~~ .php
$elevator = new Elevator([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7], 3, 0, 'foo/bar');
$elevator_str = $elevator . "";
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$elevator = [
    'up' => null,
    "" => 'foo/bar',
    'down' => 'foo/bar/2'
];
~~~

~~~ .php
$elevator_str = '<span>▲</span> <a href="foo/bar">◆</a> <a href="foo/bar/2">▼</a>';
~~~

To create horizontal elevator:

~~~ .php
$elevator = new Elevator([0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7], 3, 0, 'foo/bar', [
    'direction' => [
        '-1' => 'previous', // ← default is `up`
        '0' => "", // ← default is ``
        '1' => 'next' // ← default is `down`
    ],
    'union' => [
        // previous link
        '-1' => [
            1 => '&#x25C0;' // union content
        ],
        // next link
        '1' => [
            1 => '&#x25B6;'
        ]
    ]
]);

$elevator_str = $elevator . "";
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$elevator = [
    'previous' => null,
    "" => 'foo/bar',
    'next' => 'foo/bar/2'
];
~~~

~~~ .php
$elevator_str = '<span>◀</span> <a href="foo/bar">◆</a> <a href="foo/bar/2">▶</a>';
~~~

